		<div>I don't see killing important NPCs as a problem guys. Look at EQ, you could kill all the NPCs but no one ever really bothered to do it. It was certainly too hard to use as a method of grief.<br />
<br />
In fact the only time someone has messed up an NPC for me is when an evil guy runs through a good town and the merchants go to chase him, they take forever to get back to their spots and keep telling you "I'm busy" until they do so.<br />
<br />
Like I said earlier though, this is a ganker's dream though. And it doesn't even have to be a raid against a town. The "small outposts" that a previous poster mentioned are also nearly undoable.<br />
<br />
How many people remember killing Freeport gaurds with their Paladin/evil character? Or Neriak guards as a lowbie?<br />
<br />
All those kinds of things in WoW will flag you as pvp, and then anyone who wants to can bide their time and gank you at leisure at the worst moment for you.<br />
<br />
What does that mean? It means no one will kill the gaurds until there is some seriously uber reward for it.<br />
<br />
This is what bothers me, it's taking part of the game away.</div>
